'''國民保健署'''（{{Lang-en|'''National Health Service'''}}，簡稱'''NHS'''），是[[英國|英國]]以下四大公營醫療系統的統稱：
* [[國民保健署_(英格蘭)|英格蘭國民保健署]]（National Health Service）
* {{link-en|北愛爾蘭保健及社會服務署|Health and Social Care (Northern Ireland)}}（Health and Social Care in Northern Ireland，HSCNI）
* {{link-en|蘇格蘭國民保健署|NHS Scotland}}（NHS Scotland）
* {{link-en|威爾斯國民保健署|NHS Wales}}（NHS Wales）

國民保健署的經費主要來自全國中央稅收，用以向公眾提供一系列的醫療保健服務，合法居於英國的人士可以免費享用當中大部份的服務。國民保健署旗下四大系統各自獨立運作，並擁有各自的管理層、規例和法定權力，互不從屬。

雖然只有[[英格蘭|英格蘭]]地區的公營醫療系統是正式稱為「國民保健署」，但全國四大公營醫療系統都被普遍稱為「NHS」。國民保健署最初經過1946年、1947年和1948年的多項立法工作，最終由當時的[[英國工黨|工黨]]政府在1948年設立。NHS威爾斯原本屬於英格蘭國民保健署的一部份，但管理權到1969年分拆到[[威爾斯事務大臣|威爾斯事務大臣]]手上，1999年再進一步下放到[[威爾斯政府|威爾斯政府]]。

==适用人群==
英国居民有权在NHS接受免费医疗服务，但牙医不在此列。拥有[[欧洲健康保险卡|欧洲健康保险卡]]的欧洲公民也可在NHS接受免费医疗服务<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/society/reality-check/2015/aug/11/are-foreigners-gaming-nhs-pay-medical-treatment-abroad-ehic|title=Are foreigners really gaming the NHS to pay for their medical treatment abroad?|first=Alberto|last=Nardelli|date=11 August 2015|website=the Guardian|accessdate=2018-12-20|archive-date=2020-11-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201108224838/http://www.theguardian.com/society/reality-check/2015/aug/11/are-foreigners-gaming-nhs-pay-medical-treatment-abroad-ehic|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

此外多数国家的移民在申请超过6个月的长期签证时会支付一笔医疗费（2018年为400镑/年，但对学生有减免，约100-300镑<ref>{{cite news|title=Increase in health charge paid by temporary migrants|url=http://www.onmedica.com/newsArticle.aspx?id=b53c8bce-517e-4e85-9fac-abd7a07e908b|accessdate=2 April 2018|publisher=OnMedica|date=6 February 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180206143611/http://www.onmedica.com/NewsArticle.aspx?id=b53c8bce-517e-4e85-9fac-abd7a07e908b|archive-date=2018-02-06|dead-url=yes}}</ref>），由此也可以在英国享受NHS服务<ref>Bruno Rodrigues, [http://www.immigration.media/important-nhs-charges-in-visa-applications/ "Important NHS charges in visa applications"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.immigration.media/important-nhs-charges-in-visa-applications/ |date=20181221041359 }}, "Immigration Media", 18 March 2015</ref>。

==問題==
===資金===
[[File:NHS_Spending_1948-2014.png|thumb]]
NHS98.8%的資金來自英國国民保险和其他稅收，只有很小一部分來自病人為特定項目繳付的錢<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.kingsfund.org.uk/projects/nhs-in-a-nutshell/how-nhs-funded |title=How the NHS is funded |website=TheKing'sFund |date=15 January 2016 |author= |accessdate=6 June 2016 |archive-date=2016-06-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160621015923/http://www.kingsfund.org.uk/projects/nhs-in-a-nutshell/how-nhs-funded |dead-url=yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rcplondon.ac.uk/guidelines-policy/underfunded-underdoctored-overstretched-nhs-2016|title=Underfunded, underdoctored, overstretched: The NHS in 2016|date=21 September 2016|publisher=|accessdate=2019-06-01|archive-date=2020-04-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200405042734/https://www.rcplondon.ac.uk/guidelines-policy/underfunded-underdoctored-overstretched-nhs-2016|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。自建立以來，NHS的開銷就逐年增加，英國政府因此決定縮減開支，2010年時決定將每年增長額度限定到1%<ref name=bbc10022017>{{cite news|title=10 charts that show why the NHS is in trouble|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/health-38887694|accessdate=10 February 2017|publisher=BBC News|date=8 February 2017|archive-date=2017-02-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170210134916/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/health-38887694|dead-url=no}}</ref>。因此自2019年開始NHS將不再提供部分服務<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/voices/nhs-funding-tax-surgery-stopped-minor-operations-learn-surgery-on-self-a8425306.html|title='Here's a step-by-step guide to saving the NHS, starting with amateur surgery at home'|publisher=|accessdate=2019-06-01|archive-date=2020-05-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200502030025/https://www.independent.co.uk/voices/nhs-funding-tax-surgery-stopped-minor-operations-learn-surgery-on-self-a8425306.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

60%的NHS預算花在了僱員工資上，藥物和設備開銷各佔20%。因政府所縮減銷，醫生和護士工會表示這一舉措使得NHS員工工資縮水，因此要求政府取消每年增長額度限制<ref>[https://www.theguardian.com/society/2017/jun/19/health-unions-urge-theresa-may-to-ditch-nhs-pay-cap Health unions urge Theresa May to ditch NHS pay cap] {{Wayback|url=https://www.theguardian.com/society/2017/jun/19/health-unions-urge-theresa-may-to-ditch-nhs-pay-cap |date=20201112003010 }} ''[[The_Guardian|The Guardian]]''</ref>。此外部分病人，如癌症病人也因得不到後續治療而面臨病情加劇的危險。<ref>[https://www.theguardian.com/society/2018/jun/02/nhs-cancer-patients-failing-to-be-correctly-monitored NHS cancer patients 'failing to be correctly monitored'] {{Wayback|url=https://www.theguardian.com/society/2018/jun/02/nhs-cancer-patients-failing-to-be-correctly-monitored |date=20201109024548 }} ''[[The_Guardian|The Guardian]]''</ref>

===心理健康===

需要心理健康服務的病人需要等待的時間過久。[[英國皇家精神科醫學院|英國皇家精神科醫學院]]發現有些病人甚至需要等待13個月才能得到治療。<ref>[https://www.theguardian.com/society/2018/oct/09/mental-health-patients-waiting-nhs-treatment-delays Delays in NHS mental health treatment 'ruining lives'] {{Wayback|url=https://www.theguardian.com/society/2018/oct/09/mental-health-patients-waiting-nhs-treatment-delays |date=20201118182314 }} ''[[The_Guardian|The Guardian]]''</ref>
===手术===
需要接受常规手术的病人等待时间自2000年以来急剧增加。2019年7月英格兰平均等待时间为8周。但需要等待12个月以上的病人从1980年代的20余万缩减到2019年的不到两千人<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.england.nhs.uk/statistics/statistical-work-areas/rtt-waiting-times/|title=Statistics » Consultant-led Referral to Treatment Waiting Times|website=www.england.nhs.uk|access-date=2019-09-30|archive-date=2021-01-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210114173902/https://www.england.nhs.uk/statistics/statistical-work-areas/rtt-waiting-times/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。不過由于NHS资金、床位短缺，需要等待的病人数量时有回升。<ref>[https://www.theguardian.com/society/2018/sep/07/nhs-cancels-14-of-operations-at-last-minute-research-finds NHS cancels 14% of operations at last minute, research finds] {{Wayback|url=https://www.theguardian.com/society/2018/sep/07/nhs-cancels-14-of-operations-at-last-minute-research-finds |date=20201112020204 }} ''[[The_Guardian|The Guardian]]''</ref>

